SEC. 2. Section 5 of the same law is hereby amended to read as follows:

ГўВҖВңSEC. 5.

Functions of the PESO. ГўВҖВ“

The PESO shall have the following functions:

ГўВҖВң(a) Encourage employers to submit to the PESO on a regular basis a list of job vacancies in their respective establishments in order to facilitate the exchange of labor market information between job seekers and employers by providing employment information services to job seekers, both for local and overseas employment, and recruitment assistance to employers;

ГўВҖВң(b) Develop and administer testing and evaluation instruments for effective job selection, training and counselling;

ГўВҖВң(c) Provide persons with entrepreneurship qualities, access to the various livelihood and self-employment programs offered by both government and nongovernment organizations at the provincial, city, municipal and barangay levels by undertaking referrals for such program;

ГўВҖВң(d) Undertake employability enhancement trainings or seminars for job seekers, as well as those who would like to change career or enhance their employability;

ГўВҖВң(e) Provide employment or occupational counselling, career guidance, mass motivation and values development activities;

ГўВҖВң(f) Conduct pre-employment counselling and orientation to prospective local and, most especially, overseas workers;

ГўВҖВң(g) Provide reintegration assistance services to returning Filipino migrant workers;

ГўВҖВң(h) Prepare and submit to the local sanggunian an annual employment plan and budget including other regular funding sources and budgetary support of the PESO; and

ГўВҖВң(i) Perform such functions as to fully carry out the objectives of this Act.ГўВҖВқ

SEC. 4. Section 7 of the same law is hereby amended to read as follows:

ГўВҖВңSEC. 7.

Role of the DOLE and the LGUs.

ГўВҖВ“ The LGUs, in coordination with the DOLE, shall establish the PESO.

ГўВҖВңIt shall be the responsibility of the DOLE to:

ГўВҖВң(a) Provide technical supervision, coordination and capacity-building to the PESO;

ГўВҖВң(b) Establish and maintain a computerized human resource and job registries to facilitate the provision and packaging of employment assistance to PESO clients and the setting-up of intra- and interГӮregional job clearance systems as part of the overall employment network;

ГўВҖВң(c) Provide technical assistance and allied support services to the PESO including, but not limited to, the training of PESO personnel in the various aspects of employment facilitation functions;

ГўВҖВң(d) Set standards for the establishment and operation of the PESO office, and qualification standards for the PESO personnel;

ГўВҖВң(e) Extend other packages of employment services to the LGU, NGO or EI concerned, including the conduct of job lairs, career development seminars, and other activities; and

ГўВҖВң(i) Operate and maintain the PESO;

ГўВҖВң(ii) Ensure compliance with the operational standards set by the DOLE;

ГўВҖВң(iii) Extend such assistance and services as may be necessary in the promotion of employment within the area of jurisdiction; and

ГўВҖВң(iv) Submit to the DOLE periodic: performance and accomplishment reports.ГўВҖВқ
